/*********************************************************************************
* All characters are generated by paint brush. Following is the procedure: -
* 1. Open "Paint Brush"
* 2. Go to Image>Attributes>width = 32, Height = 32, Select Unit = "Pixels" and 
*    Select Colors = "Black and White".
* 3. Click "OK".
* 4. Click "Yes" for next warning message.
* 5. Select "Text" button and set the area to draw.
* 6. Type the digit "1".
* 7. Selcect the text and then select the following in text toolbar -- 
*    "Lucida Console", "26", "Western", "Bold".
* 8. Go to Image>Flip/Rotate>Flip Horizontal>OK.
* 9. Go to Image>Flip/Rotate>Rotate by 90deg>OK.
* 10. Save image in "BMP_Trial/32X32".
* 11. Run the VC++ code for generation of array, by changin the suitable file
*     name of BMP image, stored in 32X32 folder.
* 12. Remove 16 bytes (all 0xFF) from begining and end of each array. This is
      to remove white space.
**********************************************************************************/
